{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0171WNc7NoqnQKiYToCUzKB1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 7.2: Resume After Circuit Breaker\n2\t\n3\tStatus: review\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want to resume execution after the circuit breaker halts,\n11\tso that I can apply manual fixes and re-run verification without losing previous findings.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** workflow state has `circuit_breaker.triggered = true` and `phase = 'circuit-breaker'`\n16\t   **When** `codeharness run --resume` executes\n17\t   **Then** `circuit_breaker.triggered` is reset to `false`, `circuit_breaker.reason` is reset to `null`, and `phase` is reset to `'idle'`\n18\t   **And** engine execution proceeds (does not early-exit)\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** workflow state has `circuit_breaker.triggered = true`\n22\t   **When** `codeharness run --resume` executes\n23\t   **Then** `circuit_breaker.score_history` is preserved (not cleared) so the developer can see cumulative progress\n24\t   **And** `evaluator_scores` array is preserved (not cleared) so the engine has full history\n25\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t3. **Given** workflow state has `phase = 'circuit-breaker'` and `iteration = 5`\n28\t   **When** `codeharness run --resume` executes\n29\t   **Then** the engine resumes from the verify step of the loop block (not from the beginning of the workflow)\n30\t   **And** the verify task re-runs the entire artifact from scratch (full re-verification, not incremental)\n31\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t4. **Given** circuit breaker halted with evaluator findings from previous iterations\n34\t   **When** `codeharness run --resume` executes\n35\t   **Then** the previous evaluator findings are available in the workflow state for injection into retry prompts\n36\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n37\t\n38\t5. **Given** `codeharness run` is invoked without `--resume` and state has `phase = 'circuit-breaker'`\n39\t   **When** the engine reads state\n40\t   **Then** the engine does NOT automatically reset the circuit breaker\n41\t   **And** it returns immediately (the circuit breaker halt is respected)\n42\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n43\t\n44\t6. **Given** `codeharness run --resume` resets the circuit breaker and verify runs again\n45\t   **When** the evaluator produces a new verdict with no improvement\n46\t   **Then** the circuit breaker triggers again (scores did not improve) with updated score history\n47\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n48\t\n49\t7. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n50\t   **When** the build completes\n51\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero errors\n52\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n53\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n54\t\n55\t8. **Given** unit tests for the resume-after-circuit-breaker functionality\n56\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n57\t   **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for the new/modified code covering: circuit breaker reset on resume, score history preservation, phase transition from circuit-breaker to idle, interaction with executeWorkflow when resuming, non-resume behavior (circuit breaker respected)\n58\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n59\t\n60\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n61\t\n62\t- [x] Task 1: Update `--resume` handling in `src/commands/run.ts` to reset circuit breaker state (AC: #1, #2, #5)\n63\t  - [x] In the `--resume` block (line 134), add a check for `phase === 'circuit-breaker'`\n64\t  - [x] When phase is `circuit-breaker`, reset: `circuit_breaker.triggered = false`, `circuit_breaker.reason = null`, `phase = 'idle'`\n65\t  - [x] Preserve `circuit_breaker.score_history` and `evaluator_scores` (do NOT clear them)\n66\t  - [x] Log an info message: `'Resuming after circuit breaker — previous findings preserved'`\n67\t  - [x] Ensure plain `codeharness run` (without `--resume`) does NOT reset circuit breaker\n68\t\n69\t- [x] Task 2: Ensure workflow engine handles resumed circuit-breaker state correctly (AC: #3, #4, #6)\n70\t  - [x] Verify that `executeWorkflow` with `phase = 'idle'` and existing `iteration > 0` correctly resumes into the loop block\n71\t  - [x] Verify that the loop block's crash-recovery logic (checking `isLoopTaskCompleted`) allows re-entry at the verify step\n72\t  - [x] Verify that `evaluator_scores` history feeds into circuit breaker evaluation on subsequent iterations\n73\t  - [x] No changes to `workflow-engine.ts` needed — the existing resume logic handles this correctly.\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests in `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` (AC: #7, #8)\n76\t  - [x] Test: `--resume` with `phase = 'circuit-breaker'` resets triggered/reason/phase but keeps score_history and evaluator_scores\n77\t  - [x] Test: `--resume` with `phase = 'circuit-breaker'` logs appropriate info message\n78\t  - [x] Test: `--resume` with `phase = 'completed'` still works as before (regression test)\n79\t  - [x] Test: `--resume` with `phase = 'idle'` does not write state (regression test)\n80\t  - [x] Test: without `--resume`, `phase = 'circuit-breaker'` is NOT reset\n81\t  - [x] Verify `npm run build` passes\n82\t  - [x] Verify no regressions in existing tests\n83\t\n84\t## Dev Notes\n85\t\n86\t### Current Resume Behavior (What Exists)\n87\t\n88\tThe `--resume` flag in `run.ts` currently handles ONE case: when `phase === 'completed'`, it resets to `'idle'`. This story extends `--resume` to also handle `phase === 'circuit-breaker'`.\n89\t\n90\t```typescript\n91\t// Current code (line 134 of run.ts):\n92\tif (options.resume) {\n93\t  const currentState = readWorkflowState(projectDir);\n94\t  if (currentState.phase === 'completed') {\n95\t    writeWorkflowState({ ...currentState, phase: 'idle' }, projectDir);\n96\t    info('Resuming from completed state — phase reset to idle', outputOpts);\n97\t  }\n98\t}\n99\t```\n100\t\n101\tThe change is to add an `else if` for `phase === 'circuit-breaker'`:\n102\t\n103\t```typescript\n104\tif (options.resume) {\n105\t  const currentState = readWorkflowState(projectDir);\n106\t  if (currentState.phase === 'completed') {\n107\t    writeWorkflowState({ ...currentState, phase: 'idle' }, projectDir);\n108\t    info('Resuming from completed state — phase reset to idle', outputOpts);\n109\t  } else if (currentState.phase === 'circuit-breaker') {\n110\t    writeWorkflowState({\n111\t      ...currentState,\n112\t      phase: 'idle',\n113\t      circuit_breaker: {\n114\t        ...currentState.circuit_breaker,\n115\t        triggered: false,\n116\t        reason: null,\n117\t        // score_history is PRESERVED\n118\t      },\n119\t    }, projectDir);\n120\t    info('Resuming after circuit breaker — previous findings preserved', outputOpts);\n121\t  }\n122\t}\n123\t```\n124\t\n125\t### Why No Changes to workflow-engine.ts\n126\t\n127\tThe workflow engine already supports resume from a partially-completed state:\n128\t- `executeWorkflow` reads state and skips completed tasks via `isTaskCompleted()` / `isLoopTaskCompleted()`\n129\t- `executeLoopBlock` checks if the current iteration is fully done and advances or resumes accordingly\n130\t- The circuit breaker check at line 666 only triggers if `circuit_breaker.triggered === true` — after reset, it won't fire\n131\t- `evaluator_scores` are preserved, so the circuit breaker can still detect stagnation on the next iteration\n132\t\n133\tThe only code change needed is in `run.ts` to reset the circuit breaker state before the engine runs.\n134\t\n135\t### State Preservation Strategy\n136\t\n137\t**Preserved on resume:**\n138\t- `evaluator_scores` — full history of all evaluator verdicts. The circuit breaker needs this for stagnation detection.\n139\t- `circuit_breaker.score_history` — cumulative passed counts. Useful for developer visibility.\n140\t- `tasks_completed` — checkpoint history. The engine uses this for crash recovery.\n141\t- `iteration` — current iteration number. The engine continues from here.\n142\t\n143\t**Reset on resume:**\n144\t- `circuit_breaker.triggered` — set to `false` so the engine continues\n145\t- `circuit_breaker.reason` — set to `null` (no longer halted)\n146\t- `phase` — set to `'idle'` so `executeWorkflow` doesn't early-exit\n147\t\n148\t### Edge Case: Re-triggering\n149\t\n150\tAfter resume, if the evaluator runs again and scores don't improve, the circuit breaker will trigger again because `evaluator_scores` is preserved. The new score will be appended, and `evaluateProgress()` will compare the new score to the last pre-halt score. If no improvement, `halt: true` is returned again. This is correct behavior — it prevents infinite manual-fix-then-resume loops that don't actually fix anything.\n151\t\n152\t### Dependencies\n153\t\n154\t- **Modified file:** `src/commands/run.ts` — extend `--resume` handling\n155\t- **Modified file:** `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — add new test cases\n156\t- **No new files needed**\n157\t- **No new dependencies**\n158\t\n159\t### File Structure\n160\t\n161\t- Modified: `src/commands/run.ts` (~10 lines added)\n162\t- Modified: `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` (~60-80 lines added)\n163\t\n164\t### Testing Standards\n165\t\n166\t- Framework: `vitest` (already configured)\n167\t- Pattern: co-located tests in `src/commands/__tests__/`\n168\t- Coverage target: 80%+\n169\t- The existing test file already mocks `readWorkflowState`, `writeWorkflowState`, and `executeWorkflow` — follow the same pattern\n170\t- The existing test at line 424 (`--resume resets completed phase to idle`) is the template for the new tests\n171\t\n172\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n173\t\n174\t- **Do NOT clear evaluator_scores on resume** — the circuit breaker needs the full history to detect continued stagnation\n175\t- **Do NOT clear score_history on resume** — this is valuable for developer debugging\n176\t- **Do NOT modify workflow-engine.ts unless tests prove the existing resume logic is broken** — the engine already handles re-entry correctly\n177\t- **Do NOT add a new CLI flag** — `--resume` already exists and should handle this case\n178\t- **Do NOT reset `tasks_completed`** — the engine needs this for crash recovery\n179\t- **Do NOT reset `iteration`** — the engine should continue from the current iteration, not start over\n180\t\n181\t### Project Structure Notes\n182\t\n183\t- `src/commands/run.ts` already imports all needed functions\n184\t- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` already has the full mock setup needed\n185\t- No new directories or modules needed\n186\t- Follows the existing pattern of extending `--resume` behavior\n187\t\n188\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n189\t\n190\tFrom story 7-1 (circuit breaker module):\n191\t- `evaluateProgress()` in `circuit-breaker.ts` is pure computation — takes `EvaluatorScore[]`, returns `CircuitBreakerDecision`\n192\t- Stagnation detected when `passed` count doesn't increase for 2+ consecutive iterations\n193\t- `CircuitBreakerDecision.halt === true` includes `remainingFailures` and `scoreHistory`\n194\t- The engine records circuit breaker state in `workflow-state.yaml` and sets `phase = 'circuit-breaker'`\n195\t\n196\tFrom story 5-3 (crash recovery):\n197\t- `readWorkflowState()` / `writeWorkflowState()` handle YAML persistence\n198\t- `executeWorkflow` reads state at startup and skips completed tasks\n199\t- Loop block resume uses `isLoopTaskCompleted()` to determine which tasks need re-execution\n200\t\n201\tFrom story 5-2 (loop blocks):\n202\t- `executeLoopBlock` checks `circuit_breaker.triggered` at line 666 to decide whether to halt\n203\t- The loop iterates: retry (per-story, failed only) -> verify (per-run) -> check termination\n204\t- After resume with `triggered = false`, the loop will continue normally\n205\t\n206\t### Git Intelligence\n207\t\n208\tRecent commits follow: `feat: story {key} — {description}`. This story modifies existing files only (no new modules). The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM `.js` extensions in import paths. Tests use vitest with vi.mock patterns.\n209\t\n210\t### References\n211\t\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 7.2: Resume After Circuit Breaker]\n213\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR35]\n214\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — circuit-breaker]\n215\t- [Source: src/commands/run.ts — --resume handling (lines 133-140)]\n216\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — circuit breaker check (lines 666-669)]\n217\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-engine.ts — loop block execution (lines 447-672)]\n218\t- [Source: src/lib/circuit-breaker.ts — evaluateProgress()]\n219\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-state.ts — CircuitBreakerState, WorkflowState types]\n220\t- [Source: src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts — existing --resume tests (lines 424-468)]\n221\t- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module.md — predecessor story]\n222\t\n223\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n224\t## Verification Requirements\n225\t\n226\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/7-2-resume-after-circuit-breaker-proof.md)\n227\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n228\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n229\t\n230\t## Documentation Requirements\n231\t\n232\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n233\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/7-2-resume-after-circuit-breaker.md\n234\t\n235\t## Testing Requirements\n236\t\n237\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n238\t- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n239\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n240\t\n241\t## Dev Agent Record\n242\t\n243\t### Agent Model Used\n244\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n245\t\n246\t### Debug Log References\n247\tN/A — no debug issues encountered.\n248\t\n249\t### Completion Notes List\n250\t- Task 1: Added `else if (currentState.phase === 'circuit-breaker')` branch in the `--resume` handler in `run.ts`. Resets `triggered` to `false`, `reason` to `null`, and `phase` to `'idle'` while preserving `score_history`, `evaluator_scores`, `tasks_completed`, and `iteration`.\n251\t- Task 2: Verified existing workflow engine handles resumed state correctly — no changes to `workflow-engine.ts` needed.\n252\t- Task 3: Added 5 new test cases covering all acceptance criteria. All 4130 unit tests pass (32 in run.test.ts). Build succeeds with zero errors.\n253\t\n254\t### File List\n255\t- `src/commands/run.ts` — extended `--resume` handler (~10 lines added)\n256\t- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — 5 new test cases (~95 lines added)\n257\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01QYotpFMACcHiddivScxr1W","session_id":"f80ae629-5ae7-4b25-aa2b-80283cb9a6d8","uuid":"b1216e66-e3dc-49d9-995b-c7485dda7640","timestamp":"2026-04-03T01:31:53.539Z"}
