tputs: `npm run test:unit` (~80 lines), `npx vitest --coverage | tail -60` (~60 lines), `npx vitest --reporter=verbose` (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: vitest coverage run twice with different grep patterns; vitest verbose run twice for different test suites\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — verification (2026-04-03T01:17)\n\n- **AGENTS.md stale**: `src/lib/AGENTS.md` didn't list `circuit-breaker.ts`. Added entry as workaround — doc gap from dev agent.\n- **Proof format mismatch**: First proof used `**Verdict:** PASS` format but `codeharness verify` expected `— PASS` in heading. Rewrote.\n- **Coverage visibility**: vitest coverage table truncates filenames, required multiple grep attempts.\n- **Workflow engine comment typo**: Line 619 has `/ Circuit breaker:` (missing second slash). Minor.\n- **Verification gaps**: None. All 10 ACs fully covered.\n\n## Token Report — verification\n- Total tool calls: 19\n- By tool: Bash: 12, Read: 3, Edit: 1, Grep: 3, Write: 2\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --reporter=verbose` (~40 lines), `ls verification/` (~136 lines), `npx vitest --coverage` (~60 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: 3 attempts to extract coverage (grep refinement), 2 runs of `codeharness verify`\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — code-review (2026-04-03T01:10)\n\n- **HIGH fixed:** Integration test used mock mutation instead of testing real `evaluateProgress()` code path. Rewrote test to verify actual integration.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Old test comment inaccurate (\"triggered after dispatchCount>=2\"). Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM fixed:** Mock mutation was dead code, overwritten by real `evaluateProgress()`. Removed.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Test for all-pass-with-stagnation scenario can't occur in production.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** No input validation on `EvaluatorScore` fields (trusts upstream).\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `remainingFailures` includes `unknown` as failures.\n- Coverage: 96.81% overall, circuit-breaker.ts at 100%, all files above 80%.\n\n## Token Report — code-review\n- Total tool calls: 21\n- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 7, Edit: 2, Grep: 4, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~60 lines), `git diff` (~80 lines), `npm run build` (~20 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: one extra grep with wrong regex pattern\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — dev-story (2026-04-03T01:02)\n\n- **Test regressions from integration:** Three existing workflow-engine tests broke because mock evaluator returned same `passed: 1` every iteration, triggering stagnation. Fixed with `makeProgressingFailVerdict()` helper.\n- **remainingFailures is approximate:** Returns placeholder indices `[1..failCount]` not specific AC numbers — engine only stores aggregate `EvaluatorScore`.\n\n## Token Report — dev-story\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 5, Edit: 5, Write: 2, Grep: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm run test:unit` (~15 lines), `npm run build` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n- Redundant operations: none\n\n### 7-1-score-based-circuit-breaker-module — create-story (2026-04-03T00:57)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- `config.yaml` referenced in `workflow.yaml` does not exist at `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml`. Variables not resolvable. Proceeded without them.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Epic ACs sparse (one BDD block). Expanded to 10 discrete, testable ACs based on FR32-34 and architecture.\n- `remainingFailures` AC: `EvaluatorScore` only has aggregate counts, not per-AC findings. Documented limitation.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- None truly untestable — all test-provable.\n- Tightened \"evaluation in <100ms\" to <5ms based on architecture patterns.\n\n**Observations:**\n- workflow-engine already checks `circuit_breaker.triggered` at line 651 but never sets it. This story closes that gap.\n- `CircuitBreakerState` interface already exists 